		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />i have been pondering an idea. i would like to setup a website with a dynamic php script to aid in the writing of an NES programming book. it would start with the basics of 6502 and then gradually move on to NES specific information. It would include working examples, pointers, tips, and an appendix with usefull routines for the NES. I would like this to be a community project with input from anyone who wants to contribute. is anyone interested in helping me with this? if anyone is interested i will setup a website with a script to aid in the development of this online book. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

